correctness.rationale: Major factual and schema issues throughout. Key errors: (1) aldSystem.aldMethod set to PEALD, but the article reports photo-ALD (UV-assisted, no plasma). plasmaPower is provided with null numericValue, and plasma was not used. (2) processParameters.dosingTime and purgeTime units are wrong: article specifies 2 s (reactant pulses) and 8 s (evacuation), but extraction uses 2.0 and 8.0 with unit MilliSEC (ms); values should be 2000 ms and 8000 ms if using ms. purgeTime.coReactant has null numericValue. (3) Many required numeric fields are null, violating the schema and the “no null” rule: pressure.quantityValue.numericValue, thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.values[0].value.quantityValue.numericValue, thicknessControl.numberofCycles.quantityValue.numericValue, thicknessControl.filmThickness.quantityValue.numericValue, nucleationPeriod.quantityValue.numericValue, flowRates.purgingGasFlow.quantityValue.numericValue, processParameters.filmThickness.quantityValue.numericValue, multiple materialProperties (uniformity, conformality, elementalConcentration, roughness, filmDensity), and deviceProperties fields. (4) ReactantSelection.purgingGas is set to argon without explicit support in the text (only carrier gas argon is stated). (5) Flow rates: the article reports 67.0 and 17.5 (likely μmol/min, OCR’d as l mol/min) controlled via bubbler temperature; extraction encodes 67.0 and 17.5 with unit SCM-PER-MIN (standard cubic meter per min), which is incorrect and mismatched to the reported molar flow. (6) Electrical resistivity value is misconverted: article states 6.9×10^-4 Ω·cm; extraction gives 0.00069 Ω·m (should be 6.9×10^-6 Ω·m). (7) Doping by B2H6 is central to one process, but B2H6 is not captured in reactantSelection or supercycleDesign; the resistivity reported corresponds to B-doped films, so the process is semantically inconsistent. (8) SupercycleDesign provided without textual support; saturation set to True without evidence. (9) Several placeholders like "Not Found" are used and many values are guessed (e.g., atomicRatio 1:1, reproducibility True) without traceability. Overall, the extraction has multiple incorrect values, missing data, unjustified assumptions, and schema violations. Properties to correct/review: aldMethod (photo-ALD not PEALD), remove plasmaPower or set appropriately, fix dosing/purge times units, flow rate units/values, resistivity units, add B2H6 details for doped process, and eliminate null numericValues or omit optional fields not reported.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains multiple schema violations and factual errors. Key issues: (1) Wrong ALD method: set to PEALD despite no plasma being used; the article reports photo-ALD with a mercury UV lamp. Plasma power is included with null numericValue, conflicting with the method and violating the schema. (2) Missing/invalid required process parameters: pressure is required but given with numericValue=None; thicknessControl requires growthPerCycle values, numberofCycles, and filmThickness, but all have numericValue=None; nucleationPeriod is present with None. These are schema-invalid. (3) Dosing/purge times are incorrect: article gives 2 s doses and 8 s purges; schema requires milliseconds but the extraction uses 2.0 and 8.0 with unit MilliSEC (should be 2000 ms and 8000 ms), and the co-reactant purge is left None. (4) Reactants and process design are incomplete: B2H6 dopant and its injection-cycle sequences (every 1,2,4,6,8,12 cycles) are not captured; supercycle/doping design is not represented; UV irradiation conditions (intensity ratios, wavelengths, shutter sequences) are not captured anywhere. (5) Flow rate units likely mismatched: article reports ‘… mol/min’ (likely μmol/min), but the extraction uses sccm units; traceability and unit consistency are weak. (6) Electrical property error: resistivity from the article is 6.9e-4 ohm-cm; the extraction reports 6.9e-4 ohm-m, a 100× error. Carrier density and mobility are left None. (7) Material properties contain ungrounded or null values: atomic ratio set to 1:1 without support from the text; uniformity, conformality, roughness, film density, optical properties are provided with numericValue=None, violating schema. (8) Device properties are required by the schema but the article has no devices; the extraction fills them with None, violating schema and lacking traceability. (9) Multiple processes are described in the article (undoped with varying UV intensity/sequence and boron-doped with varying B2H6/DEZ cycle ratios), but only a single process is extracted. To improve, correct the method (likely TALD with UV assistance), remove optional fields with nulls or supply valid numbers with QUDT-compliant units, add pressure if reported (or omit if schema allowed), fix dosing/purge times (2000 ms, 8000 ms), add B2H6 as a dopant strategy with its injection cycles, represent distinct undoped and doped processes separately, correct resistivity units, and avoid unsubstantiated composition values.
